{"questionId":"17591","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Casanova restaurant offers a set menu where a customer chooses <strong>one</strong> of the following meals: pasta, fish or shrimp.</p>\n<p>The manager surveyed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>150</mn></math> customers and recorded the customer’s age and chosen meal. The data is shown in the following table.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/cdde0674462189e294efbc91e15fc4d16917367e.png\"></p>\n<p>A <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>χ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> test was performed at the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>%</mo></math> significance level. The critical value for this test is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>605</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Write down</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>χ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> statistic.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msubsup><mi>χ</mi><mtext>calc</mtext><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">=</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>66</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>657537</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(G2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17591","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.T_1d.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the χ2 statistic.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots","Topic 4—Statistics and pr